==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Palanquin
<hw>Pal`an*quin"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>palanquin</ets>, Pg. <ets>palanquim</ets>, Javan.
<ets>palangki</ets>, OJavan. <ets>palangkan</ets>, through Prakrit fr.
Skr. <ets>parya⟦ndot⟧ka</ets>, <ets>palya⟦ndot⟧ka</ets>, bed, couch;
<ets>pari</ets> around (akin to E. pref. <ets>peri-</ets>) +
<ets>a⟦ndot⟧ka</ets> a hook, flank, probably akin to E. <ets>angle</ets>
fishing tackle. Cf. <er>Palkee</er>.]</ety> <def>An inclosed carriage or
litter, commonly about eight feet long, four feet wide, and four feet
high, borne on the shoulders of men by means of two projecting poles, --
used in <country>India</country>, <country>China</country>, etc., for
the conveyance of a single person from place to place.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>palankeen</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Palapteryx</ent>⟦br⟧
